BETWEEN THAT

00:53.453 --> 00:56.188
AND NOT FINISHING THE
CAKE ON THE DRIVE HOME,

00:56.255 --> 00:58.290
YOU'VE GOT A LOT TO
BE PROUD OF, MY FRIEND.

01:01.794 --> 01:04.062
WAIT, TODAY'S YOUR
TENTH ANNIVERSARY?

01:04.129 --> 01:07.332
SHOULDN'T IT HAVE BEEN,
LIKE, 3 MONTHS AGO?

01:07.400 --> 01:10.868
UH... NO.
NO, IT'S TODAY.

01:10.936 --> 01:12.387
CAKE DOES NOT LIE,
YOU KNOW?

01:12.455 --> 01:13.888
UNLESS IT'S
YOUR BIRTHDAY CAKE.

01:13.956 --> 01:16.324
THAT BABY'S SEEN 29 CANDLES
MORE THAN ONCE, AM I RIGHT?

01:16.392 --> 01:18.960
HA HA HA!
I THINK I AM.

01:19.027 --> 01:23.148
NO, NO. I REMEMBER EXACTLY
WHEN YOU STARTED AT I.P.S.

01:23.215 --> 01:25.049
BECAUSE THAT'S WHEN
WE STARTED DATING-

01:25.117 --> 01:26.668
SUMMER OF '95.

01:26.736 --> 01:28.202
REMEMBER,
YOU DIDN'T SHOWER MUCH

01:28.270 --> 01:30.338
'CAUSE YOU SAID
YOU WERE GRUNGE?

01:30.406 --> 01:33.108
TODAY, 3 MONTHS AGO
- WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE, REALLY?

01:33.175 --> 01:34.726
THERE'S A BIG
DIFFERENCE, DOUG, OK?

01:34.793 --> 01:36.495
A LOT OF PENSION AND
BENEFITS STUFF KICKS IN

01:36.562 --> 01:37.862
AT THE 10-YEAR MARK,

01:37.930 --> 01:40.465
WHICH MEANS I.P.S.
IS 3 MONTHS BEHIND.

01:40.533 --> 01:42.234
I'M GONNA LEAVE A
MESSAGE FOR ACCOUNTING.

01:42.301 --> 01:44.669
UH, YOU KNOW, THAT'S OK. I'LL
JUST-I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT TOMORROW.

01:44.737 --> 01:46.371
NAH.
YOU'LL NEVER DO IT.

01:47.656 --> 01:50.057
LET ME TELL YOU
A STORY.

01:52.795 --> 01:54.962
COME ON, I THOUGHT IT
WAS A REALLY GOOD MOVIE.

01:55.030 --> 01:56.564
YOU KNOW WHAT? I THINK
IT SHOULD'VE BEEN CALLED

01:56.632 --> 01:58.283
WAITING TO EXHALE
INTO MY HAND.

01:58.351 --> 02:00.085
PFFFFFT!

02:01.153 --> 02:02.721
I LOVE
WHEN YOU DO THAT.

02:04.306 --> 02:06.340
I HAD A REALLY
GREAT TIME TONIGHT.

02:06.408 --> 02:07.976
ME, TOO.

02:15.768 --> 02:17.469
SO, UH...

02:17.536 --> 02:18.837
WHAT NOW?

02:20.305 --> 02:22.140
SO, NOW YOU GO HOME.

02:22.208 --> 02:24.942
OH, COME ON, WE'VE BEEN GOING
OUT FOR, LIKE, 2 MONTHS, CARRIE.

02:25.010 --> 02:27.812
MY WHOLE BODY'S BLUE.

02:36.856 --> 02:39.824
I GOTTA GET UP EARLY
FOR WORK TOMORROW.

02:39.892 --> 02:42.110
JUST CALL IN SICK.
TELL THEM YOU CAME DOWN

02:42.178 --> 02:46.080
WITH A BAD CASE
OF DOUG-ONUCLEOSIS.

02:46.148 --> 02:47.282
GOOD NIGHT, DOUG.

02:52.971 --> 02:54.772
MMM.

02:54.840 --> 02:55.723
COME ON!

02:55.791 --> 02:57.324
GOOD NIGHT, DOUG.

03:01.530 --> 03:03.264
OK...

03:15.911 --> 03:18.613
HEY, GUYS, BEFORE I SIT
DOWN, YOU SHOULD BOTH KNOW

03:18.681 --> 03:21.215
<i>I HAVEN'T SEEN LAST
NIGHT'S MELROSE PLACE YET,</i>

03:21.283 --> 03:22.367
SO IF ANYONE
SAYS ANYTHING,

03:22.435 --> 03:23.968
I WILL
OFFICIALLY FREAK.

03:24.036 --> 03:26.387
AH, DOUG, I HATE
TO BRING IT UP NOW,

03:26.455 --> 03:28.289
BUT YOUR TAB,
IT'S RUNNING KIND OF HIGH.

03:28.357 --> 03:31.609
I CAN'T PAY A TAB IF I
DON'T HAVE A JOB, EINSTEIN.

03:31.676 --> 03:33.294
WELL, WE'RE HIRING
DOWN IN THE SUBWAY.

03:33.362 --> 03:34.729
THANKS, BUT I'M
HOLDING OUT FOR A JOB

03:34.797 --> 03:36.664
THAT DOESN'T INVOLVE
WALKING THROUGH URINE.

03:36.732 --> 03:38.916
OH, LA-DI-DA.

03:38.984 --> 03:42.052
SO, HOW ARE THINGS GOING
WITH THE NEW LADY?

03:42.120 --> 03:45.006
OH, CARRIE? GREAT. SHE'S SO
SWEET. GREAT SENSE OF HUMOR.

03:45.074 --> 03:46.807
WHEN I MAKE
MY BELLY BUTTON TALK,

03:46.876 --> 03:49.110
SHE REALLY GETS IT.

03:49.178 --> 03:51.096
AND HOW IS EVERYTHING IN...
HORIZONTAL TOWN?

03:51.163 --> 03:54.198
OH, COME ON. I DON'T LIKE TO TALK
ABOUT THAT KIND OF STUFF, ALL RIGHT?

03:54.266 --> 03:56.634
<i>OH, COME ON. I NEED SOMETHING
TO KEEP MY MIND OFF MELROSE.</i>

03:56.702 --> 03:59.270
ALL RIGHT,
WELL, LET'S JUST SAY-

03:59.338 --> 04:01.339
NOT TO GET TOO GRAPHIC-

04:01.407 --> 04:04.058
BUT I'VE GOTTEN MORE
OFF OF YOU TWO.

04:04.126 --> 04:07.111
HA HA HA! WHOA! MAN!

04:07.179 --> 04:09.380
AND YOU GUYS HAVE BEEN GOING
OUT FOR, LIKE, 2 MONTHS, RIGHT?

04:09.448 --> 04:10.949
IT'S A LITTLE ROUGH,
BUT CARRIE WANTS TO WAIT.

04:11.016 --> 04:14.953
AND I RESPECT THE FACT THAT
CARRIE'S A GOOD GIRL, YOU KNOW?

04:16.971 --> 04:18.490
WHAT WAS THAT?

04:18.557 --> 04:19.357
WHAT?

04:21.010 --> 04:22.376
WHAT'S GOING ON
HERE?

04:22.444 --> 04:25.096
WELL, WORD ON THE STREET
IS THAT WAITING...

04:25.164 --> 04:26.831
ISN'T CARRIE'S THING.

04:26.898 --> 04:28.732
YOU WATCH YOUR MOUTH. I SWEAR TO
GOD, I'LL CUT YOU 8 DIFFERENT WAYS.

04:28.800 --> 04:30.368
IT'S TRUE!
YEAH?

04:30.436 --> 04:32.270
WHO'S SHE BEEN WITH?
GIVE ME ONE NAME.

04:32.338 --> 04:33.520
SAL DeROBERTIS.

04:33.588 --> 04:35.757
SAL? I THOUGHT IT WAS
HIS BROTHER JOHNNY.

04:35.824 --> 04:38.043
<i>SAL AND JOHNNY.
HE ONLY ASKED FOR ONE NAME.</i>

04:38.110 --> 04:39.577
YOU GUYS DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT, ALL RIGHT?

04:39.645 --> 04:42.413
SHE'S A GOOD GIRL, AND SHE
WANTS TO WAIT, AND THAT'S IT!

04:42.481 --> 04:44.382
<i>OK.
IT IS "OK." YEAH.</i>

04:44.450 --> 04:46.318
<i>AND YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE?
HERE'S A MELROSE UPDATE-</i>

04:46.385 --> 04:47.519
YEAH, ALLISON
GOT AMANDA'S JOB

04:47.586 --> 04:48.520
AND SLEPT WITH BILLY
IN HER OFFICE.

04:48.587 --> 04:50.121
YEAH!

05:03.135 --> 05:04.635
UH... OW!

05:04.703 --> 05:06.187
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

05:06.254 --> 05:08.489
I'M SORRY. YOU LOOKED
UNCOMFORTABLE,

05:08.557 --> 05:09.924
